# Review & commit standards

Apply on every implementation task, code review, and when the user asks for a commit or PR.

## Before claiming done (self-review)

1. **Scope** — Smallest correct diff; no drive-by refactors or unrelated files.
2. **Architecture** — Domain ← data ← presentation; screen models do not import `*Impl`.
3. **i18n** — New UI copy in all 8 `values*` locales; composables use `stringResource`; screen models expose data, not formatted English.
4. **Design system** — Reuse `Journey*` / `FamilyLogistics*` / `JourneySemanticColors`; no raw `OutlinedTextField`, `Icons.Default`, or one-off hex colors.
5. **UX states** — Loading, error, empty handled; snackbars above `bottomBar` where applicable; `imePadding` on text-heavy screens.
6. **Tests** — Unit tests for domain/screen model changes; instrumented only for critical UI paths; fakes implement full interfaces.
7. **QA YAML** — Update `firebase-appdistribution-testcases.yaml` (bump `version`) when user-facing flows change.
8. **Secrets** — No credentials, `local.properties` values, or `google-services.json` in commits.
9. **Gradle** — Run `:composeApp:testDebugUnitTest` (and instrumented compile if UI touched) before done.

## PR checklist

- Title: imperative, feature-focused (match repo style).
- Body: summary bullets + test plan (unit / instrumented / manual).
- CI: `gh pr checks N --watch` until green before merge.
- Merge: squash to `main`; delete feature branch.
- Release: **manual only** — `gh workflow run "KMP CI" --ref main -f job=release -f version_bump=patch` (not on every PR).

## Commit rules

- Commit **only when the user explicitly asks** (or clearly requests “ship” / “commit” / “finish with release”).
- Message: 1–2 sentences, **why** not just what; use HEREDOC for formatting.
- Never: `--no-verify`, force-push to `main`, amend unless user requested and HEAD is unpushed local commit.
- Pre-commit: `git status`, `git diff`, `git log -1` for style; exclude secret files.

## Review feedback priorities (blockers first)

| Priority | Check |
|----------|--------|
| P0 | Security (RLS, auth, secrets), data loss, crash |
| P1 | i18n parity, viewer read-only violations, wrong layer imports |
| P2 | Missing tests, broken `testTag`s, Firebase YAML drift |
| P3 | Design-system drift (non-Journey controls), touch targets &lt; 48dp |
| P4 | Naming, minor style |

## Anti-patterns in review

- Hardcoded English in Kotlin UI layers.
- `stringResource` inside `LaunchedEffect` / non-`@Composable` lambdas.
- Business logic in `@Composable` bodies.
- Mixing AI read-only lists with editable CRUD without explicit UX separation.
- Phone-only layout assumptions (test wide ≥ `ScreenLayout.expandedMinWidth` when touching grocery/meal plan).
